  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). An inline requirement object (https://uofa.net/morrison/req/hemolysis-rh-criterion) is referenced in the decision rationale and exists as a named entity within the package narrative, but the top-level bindsRequirement property has been intentionally omitted, constituting a W-SI-02 incomplete profile binding defect.",
